One of the clearest shifts came in the structure of the state itself. The administration pressed ahead with mass reductions in force at the State Department, after the Supreme Court lifted injunctions that had slowed the firings. More than 1,300 employees received RIF notices, about 15% of the domestic workforce. At the same time, a 48% budget cut and reorganization took effect, stripping out programs for LGBTQ+ communities, maternal and reproductive health, and minority groups. The department\'92s annual human rights reports were rewritten to omit those topics. What had been a diplomatic corps charged with defending rights abroad was recast as a leaner, more ideological arm of \'93America first\'94 policy. Expertise was not simply lost; it was selected against.\
